description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Clinical Environmental Assistant to join Orchards Ward working 10-6 Monday to Friday with a small degree of flexibility. No weekend or night work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated individual with excellent communication skills; you will come into contact with service users so good interpersonal skills are required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to ensure the ward area is kept tidy, patient laundry is part of this role also to keep patient areas clear. The ordering of stock is completed on a weekly basis, and carrying out environmental checks and audits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At Kent and Medway NHS and Social Care Partnership Trust we understand the vital role played by cleaning staff within the NHS. Therefore, we are looking for a hard working individual to help us achieve The National Cleaning Standards.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a progressive service, we place importance on the development and well-being of our staff.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Full training and uniform is provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMichelle CoxJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressmichelle.cox11@nhs.netTelephone number01622722178&lt;/p&gt;
